00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:14,200
 It can make our soldiers invincible. 

240
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,400
 But our clan is destined to have a short lifespan. 

241
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:19,600
 If this disadvantage isn't removed, it'll be hard for us to achieve greatness. 

242
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:28,300
 If... we have the Primordial Lord, 

243
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:34,400
 Ran Qing's Seven Luminaries Jade, we'll be able to engulf the lives of others. 

244
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,600
 A life for a thousand years. 

245
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,800
 Then, we could be invincible. 

246
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:47,000
 We've sent people to the Heavenly Realm to steal the jade many times. 

247
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,800
 But all of them are no match for Ran Qing. 

248
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:54,000
 That's because she hasn't met me. 

249
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:24,300
 Xuan Ye, you killed my whole clan and tried to absorb my spiritual power. 

250
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:27,800
 I'd rather kill myself than let you have your way! 

251
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:40,800
 Live or die, it's up to me. 

252
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,000
 Your Majesty, Ran Qing is here. 

253
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,500
 Perfect timing. 

254
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:26,000
 Once you learn Eternal Darkness today, it'll be deeply embedded in your body. And it'll automatically run in it. 

255
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,700
 When you reach a profound level of this cultivation over time, 

256
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:32,600
 there's no one in the world that can handle your Asura divine power. 

257
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:38,600
 Wait until the Asura Clan rules the Three Realms, your late father will be pleased with that. 

258
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,900
- I don't want to go. 
 - Come on.

259
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,200
Come on. Listen to me.

260
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,500
Let's go.

261
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,800
How about this? Here. You take this.

262
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:57,900
You go.

263
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,500
No.

264
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:03,300
Thanks to Tang Zhou. Or else Father wouldn't agree to our marriage.

265
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:08,800
No matter what, we have to send the wedding cake to him in person as a token of appreciation. Let's go.

266
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,200
Forget about it.

267
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,200
Tortoise.

268
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,400
Be honest with me.

269
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:17,000
Do you have a history with him?

270
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:21,000
Or else why would you say it makes you feel sick when you see him?

271
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,800
I don't.

272
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:27,200
I don't know why I'll feel sick when I see him.

273
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:31,200
Speaking of which, we, divine tortoises, don't have a natural enemy.

274
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,200
Right?

275
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,400
Then, let's go.

276
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,000
No.

277
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,400
Be nice to him.

278
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,500
Tang Zhou.

279
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,500
It's him.

280
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:17,700
- It was actually him. 
 - Who?

281
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:21,800
Again?

282
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,400
Tortoise!

283
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:37,800
Tortoise! Tortoise!

284
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,100
I found you.

285
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:46,600
Come on out.

286
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,800
What's the matter?

287
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,800
Is it because you don't want to marry me anymore?

288
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:56,300
No. It's because...

289
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,400
It's because...

290
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:08,800
"Kill all those in the world who flip tortoises."

291
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,200
What does it mean?

292
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,400
Fine. I'll tell you.

293
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:24,400
Actually... before I managed to turn into human form, I was just an ordinary little tortoise.

294
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:29,200
But when I was in heaven, there was a deity who would always come and flip me over.

295
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,400
I was flipped over every which way.

296
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:33,600
Again and again.

297
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,500
He flipped me over every single day.

298
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:39,800
In heaven, there was never a day where I wasn't dizzy or felt like throwing up.

299
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:44,200
The person who flipped me... is Tang Zhou!

300
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:48,000
No wonder. Every time I see him I feel like throwing up.

301
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,100
Why are you laughing so merrily?

302
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,500
Do you think it's embarrassing?

303
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:58,500
Don't want to marry me anymore?

304
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,600
It's all the more reason for me to marry you.

305
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:17,200
So then I can protect you in the future.

306
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,600
No one will dare flip you over again.

307
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,900
Only I can flip you over.

308
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,500
Why do you have a needle and thread that mortals use?

309
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:36,000
You're not trying to learn from the hedgehogs are you?

310
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:41,000
And stick needles in your tortoiseshell so that way no one will dare flip you over again?

311
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:49,000
This... is a wedding gift I prepared for you.

312
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:53,000
How about this? Close your eyes.

313
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,400
What is it?

314
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,800
Why are you being secretive?

315
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,400
Open your eyes.

316
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:21,000
That day, when we were trapped in the cave,

317
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:26,100
I watched them cut off your tail, but I couldn't do anything about it.

318
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,800
Now, I've made one for you.

319
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:32,400
At least... it makes up for it a tiny, little bit.

320
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:44,000
Where... did you find this?

321
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:47,700
Stop asking so many questions.

322
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:50,700
Just tell me if you like it or not.

323
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:55,800
The bones inside this fox tail...

324
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:17,200
Where is your tail?

325
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:21,700
Where is your tail? Where did it go?

326
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,800
Are you a fool?

327
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:27,200
Where did it go? I don't want you to do this for me!

328
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,400
Where is your tail?

329
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:39,200
Either way, I won't reveal my true form in front of mortals.

330
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:42,000
With or without a tail, it makes no difference.

331
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,900
It's just a few vertebrae. It's okay.

332
00:25:44,900 --> 00:25:46,400
I still have my shell.

333
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:49,100
I'll be fine even if there are a few bones missing.

334
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:53,200
Look at this.

335
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:56,400
I know that you like pretty things.

336
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,000
The bones don't look good in its original form.

337
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:02,800
So I learned the way the mortals do it.

338
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:06,800
I knitted each piece onto it.

339
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,600
Don't worry.

340
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:12,800
After we get married, I'll practice diligently.

341
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:17,000
I promise... no one can bully you again in the future.

342
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:30,200
I believe you.

343
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:34,300
But... isn't our wedding tomorrow?

344
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,700
I became your bride a long time ago.

345
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,600
I can't wait until tomorrow.

346
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:22,400
Just leave the wedding planning to me.

347
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:25,800
With your condition, instead of soaking in the hot spring you had to insist on coming here.

348
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:28,200
Are you worried?

349
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:30,200
My body is just fine.

350
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,000
And I'm not worried.

351
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,000
I just wanted to come here with you

352
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:40,200
to see what a wedding looks like and understand what the process is.

353
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,800
The process is complicated.

354
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:44,700
To get the bride out of the sedan chair, the groom has to shoot arrows. Then, cross the saddle.

355
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:47,200
They have to get married and swear an oath.

356
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,600
They also have to propose a toast.

357
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:51,500
In the end, they have to tie their discarded hair together and thank the matchmaker.

358
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:53,000
That complicated?

359
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:55,600
What if something goes wrong?

360
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,200
This is a good question.

361
00:27:57,200 --> 00:28:02,400
If I make a mistake, my guess is the Leader of the Fox Clan will beat me to death in public.

362
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,300
How about this then?

363
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:07,200
Let's have a rehearsal.

364
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:11,600
After we're familiar with the process, we can still save the situation even if something goes wrong.

365
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:18,400
Yan Dan. This is the only time I've ever acted as an officiant.

366
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,400
I hope that nothing will go wrong.

367
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:23,000
But the procedures are really complicated and long.

368
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:28,000
I worry that if you're away from the hot springs for too long your body won't be able to handle it.

369
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,600
Isn't it nice that it'll take a long time?

370
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,100
What?

371
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:33,300
Nothing.

372
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:36,900
I'll manage. Don't worry.

373
00:28:36,900 --> 00:28:39,800
Yan Dan, don't you like acting?

374
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:42,200
You claim yourself to be the top actress in Yelan Mountain.

375
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:45,100
What now? Are you afraid of embarrassing yourself now?

376
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:49,900
The groom shoots three arrows to remove all the bad luck!

377
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,100
Be careful. Don't hit me!

378
00:28:56,100 --> 00:28:58,900
Play your role. Focus.

379
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:07,000
♫   I want to be the star that leads you to all corners of the world   ♫

380
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:14,100
♫   Heaven is tedious, let's go to the mortal world to experience all kinds of emotions   ♫

381
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:20,800
♫   We should learn to be a fish that swims around the world   ♫

382
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:28,400
♫   Joy and sorrow can easily be forgotten instantly when the dust washes over   ♫

383
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:32,400
♫   I have experienced the intertwined threads of love like a brocade   ♫

384
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:35,300
Bride, please step out of the sedan chair!

385
00:29:35,300 --> 00:29:41,800
♫   I'm still engrossed in the moment of flowers blooming   ♫

386
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:49,700
♫   Sometimes I'm just overwhelmed with sadness   ♫

387
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:55,400
After crossing the saddle, the whole family will be safe and well!

388
00:29:55,400 --> 00:30:00,000
♫   Unexpectedly, I can't help but share what I thought was off-limits   ♫

389
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:11,200
♫   I blame time for the mortal world's woe is on your shoulder   ♫

390
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:18,900
♫   Like the surging tides of stars, I continuously ask where the origin of love comes from   ♫

391
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:23,440
Greet the five generations to carry on the family lines!

392
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,700
♫   I'm afraid the tears brimming in the corner of my eyes will fall and blur your silhouette   ♫

393
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:29,300
♫   In my momentary childishness,   ♫

394
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:34,000
♫   I now understand that all living things wither away   ♫

395
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:37,400
Nervous because it's your first time getting married?

396
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:40,400
Groom, please lift up the bride's veil!

397
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:43,300
From now on, may you be content together forever!

398
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:48,900
♫   I blame time for the mortal world's woe is on your shoulder   ♫

399
00:30:48,900 --> 00:30:56,000
♫   Like the surging tides of stars, I continuously ask where the origin of love comes from   ♫

400
00:30:56,000 --> 00:31:03,200
♫   I'm afraid the tears brimming in the corner of my eyes will fall and blur your silhouette   ♫

401
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:06,800
♫   In my momentary childishness,   ♫

402
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:13,400
♫   with everything that I am, my path all lean towards you   ♫

403
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:22,900
♫   Counting the passing of the seasons, no matter which direction, everything moves towards you   ♫

404
00:31:22,900 --> 00:31:29,600
♫   The beauty is in the burning agarwood incense, there's still hope when the ashes settled   ♫

405
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:37,200
♫   Hear the beautiful prose with a fine beauty and a picturesque view, they pair well together   ♫

406
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:40,800
♫   Sew two hearts together and a stem sprouts forth   ♫

407
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:48,000
♫   Understand the wind, think about the rain, and do not awaken from the dream   ♫

408
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:58,300
♫   Just let me linger all day and night   ♫

409
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:08,420
Just forget about the wine.

410
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:10,860
Next is all your part.

411
00:32:11,940 --> 00:32:12,940
My part?

412
00:32:12,940 --> 00:32:15,920
According to rites, the groom and the bride have to thank the matchmaker.

413
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:18,200
But they don't have one, so they can only thank you.

414
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,320
Moreover, you've got to give them a gift in return.

415
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:22,740
Have you thought about what gift to give yet?

416
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,900
Lin Lang likes things that are flashy.

417
00:32:26,900 --> 00:32:29,720
Zi Lin likes things that are fun.

418
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,540
I've already thought of it.

419
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:13,540
It turns out that being with someone you like is such a happy thing.

420
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:24,300
Bride and Groom, please thank the matchmaker.

421
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:31,880
There you go again. Don't move, don't move.

422
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:35,780
What's wrong with Zi Lin?

423
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:38,820
He always feels nauseous and wants to throw up. He'll feel better after covering up his head.

424
00:33:38,820 --> 00:33:40,460
Yes, yes. That's right.

425
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:44,300
Why do you keep hiccupping non-stop?

426
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:51,340
Young Master Tang, thank you for making this happen.

427
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:54,000
 Bow to him. 

428
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:59,600
May you always be of one heart and never doubt your love.

429
00:34:00,860 --> 00:34:03,220
Young Master Tang, please give them your gift in return.

430
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:07,300
As for my gift, it can't fit in the Mountain Chief's Hall.

431
00:34:07,300 --> 00:34:10,780
Please, everyone, follow me outside of the hall.

432
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:16,020
What is Mountain Chief going to give them?

433
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:20,660
A kun?

434
00:34:20,660 --> 00:34:22,440
Why would you...

435
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:26,240
I've been dreaming of this mythological beast all the time lately.

436
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:32,200
Yan Dan, I need your help in order to make this happen.

437
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,420
Follow me.

438
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:11,440
♫   You always light up the long night like the stars and moon   ♫

439
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:15,680
♫   Your smile melts my cold heart   ♫

440
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:24,740
♫   No matter how the world changes, you're always by my side   ♫

441
00:35:24,740 --> 00:35:28,780
The first time when you saw the stars, I wasn't with you.

442
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:32,280
It later became a painful memory.

443
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:38,000
So... I'd like to give back to you a happy starry night.

444
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:42,320
♫   I've never said I miss you and I wonder when I fell in love with you   ♫

445
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:52,900
♫   We're entangled like agarwood intertwined into flames   ♫

446
00:35:52,900 --> 00:35:57,800
♫   It doesn’t extinguish and I've forgotten the cold wind and snow along the way   ♫

447
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:01,600
♫   I've experienced the ups and downs of the world alone   ♫

448
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:06,640
♫   Finally, I can rest in your heart   ♫

449
00:36:07,380 --> 00:36:12,120
♫   We've been together for a lifetime and gone through all the trials   ♫

450
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:16,440
♫   We won't complain as time will turn our hardship into sweetness   ♫

451
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:23,500
♫   I won't ask how long forever is, but we'll smile and laugh together   ♫

452
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:29,680
♫   Let the past be the past   ♫

453
00:36:46,580 --> 00:36:48,580
This is divine power!

454
00:36:49,300 --> 00:36:52,780
Sir, there's never been a wedding more luxurious or dignified than this one!

455
00:36:52,780 --> 00:36:54,660
Lin Lang is marrying well!

456
00:36:54,660 --> 00:36:57,100
Yes, you're right.

457
00:36:57,100 --> 00:36:58,740
Yes.

458
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:04,680
 I'd rather die within these seven days. 

459
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:06,740
 That mysterious man is under the same Shared-Fate Spell. 

460
00:37:06,740 --> 00:37:08,560
 His soul will be scattered along with mine. 

461
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:12,940
 He's using a lot of divine power, he's trying to blow himself up. 

462
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,900
Tang Zhou, don't be a fool!

463
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:18,660
Hurry, get down here!

464
00:37:27,180 --> 00:37:29,080
It's such a lovely night.

465
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:31,920
It's a good view to enjoy at night.

466
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:39,120
Mountain Chief, don't be so petty.

467
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:43,560
Tang Zhou, Yu Mo is right.

468
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,260
Your celestial vest is damaged to begin with.

469
00:37:45,260 --> 00:37:47,780
Doing this will consume more of your divine power.

470
00:37:47,780 --> 00:37:50,000
Hurry, let's go back down.

471
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:54,460
Just let me be stubborn this one time.

472
00:37:56,940 --> 00:37:58,540
Yan Dan...

473
00:38:01,740 --> 00:38:04,120
have you ever had feelings for me?

474
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:10,420
♫   I followed you across the endless seas reluctant to leave you   ♫

475
00:38:10,420 --> 00:38:12,080
I can't.

476
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:14,760
Very well.

477
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:20,120
That way, if I die, you won't feel that sad.

478
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:22,260
I won't let you die.

479
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:31,180
Yan Dan, if I survive through the seven days and that mysterious man  breaks the Shared-Fate Spell

480
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:35,040
and comes after me again, how am I going to protect you?

481
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:37,060
I'm not afraid of dying.

482
